The environment constitutes the sum total of all living (biotic) and non-living (abiotic) components—including air, water, soil, and organisms—that surround and influence life on Earth. It consists of natural systems (atmosphere, hydrosphere, lithosphere, biosphere) and human-made structures, which constantly interact and adapt. 
